natspec.author: Daccred.
natspec.details: An instance of the Soulbound token with capped supply       and tokens having their own individual expiry date.       Tokens are minted to and are pendng until receivers       pay to receive their complete token.

Unsigned(address).details: Thrown when the address passed to the verify function is not signed.

Redeemed(uint256,uint256).details: Emitted when a token is redeemed.

_getBaseURI().details: Returns already set baseURI if it exists.

balanceOf(address).details: ABTs assigned to the zero address are considered invalid, and this  function throws for queries about the zero address.
balanceOf(address).notice: Count all ABTs assigned to an owner

params.owner: An address for whom to query the balance

returns._0: The number of ABTs owned by `owner`, possibly zero

burn(uint256).details: Must emit a `event Revoke` with the `address to` field pointing to  the zero address.
burn(uint256).notice: Destroys `tokenId`. At any time, an ABT receiver must be able to  disassociate themselves from an ABT publicly through calling this  function.

constructor.details: Deploy the SoulboundWithSignature with set         total supply, priceLimit and price of an individual token.

extendExpiry(uint256,uint256).details: On every successful redemption or mint of token the       expiry of the token is extended by the duration passed       in the contract.       This should be called on expired tokens.
extendExpiry(uint256,uint256).notice: This function is expected to be called by the           SoulboundRedeemable on every mint.

params.time: Length of time to extend it with.

generateTokenURI(uint256).details: Using the `tokenId` passed, it generates a `stringified` tokenURI,       packing the baseURI and the current tokenId.       Makes use of OpenZeppelin's uint to string function.

params.tokenId: ID of token whose tokenURI is desired.

getIndividualTokenPrice().details: Return the price of one token, set by the deployer.

getPriceLimit().details: Return the highest possible price for a token.

getTimeLeft(uint256).details: Returns the time left for a token to expire.

isMinted(address,uint256).details: Returns true if token `_tokenId` was minted from this contract to `_to`.       `_to` must not be a 0 address.       `_tokenId` must be an existent token.

params._to: Address to which token `_tokenId` is minted.

isValid(uint256).details: Return true if the token is expired or false if otherwise.

issueWithSignature(address,bytes32,bytes.details: Mints a particular quantity of tokens to `to`,        on the condition that the address has been        signed by the allowlistOwner off-chain.       This will emit the {MintSoulboundToken} event       from the Soulbound.sol.

params.tokenId: Id of the tokens to mint to the `addr`.
params.tokenURI: URI of the token to be minted.

issuerOf(address,uint256).details: Since a token cannnot be minted twice.       This function returns the address that minted token `_tokenId` to `_to`,       otherwise this contract.       `_to` must not be a 0 address.       `_tokenId` must be an existent token.       Owner of _tokenId must be _to.

params._to: Address to which token `_tokenId` is minted.

mintPendingRedeemableToken(address,addre.details: Mints a pending soulbound token to `to`.       Pending tokens are minted and the receiver pays       to receive and completely mint them.
mintPendingRedeemableToken(address,addre.notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer]           and the allowlistOwner.

params._tokenExpiryDate: Set expiry date from the deployer.
params.tokenId: Id of token to be minted.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

ownerIssueWithSignature(address,bytes32,.details: Ref SoulboundCore.sol issueWithSignature       This function grants the access to only the       deployer of the contract, unlike the core       that allows the function for anyone who has a       signature signed by the allowlistOwner.       This contract can be called by the deployer of the       contract [DaccredDeployer] but is also protected       as to the allowlistOwner must be the signer of the `sig.`
ownerIssueWithSignature(address,bytes32,.notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer].

params.tokenURI: URI of token to be issued.

ownerOf(uint256).details: ABTs assigned to zero address are considered invalid, and queries  about them do throw.
ownerOf(uint256).notice: Find the address bound to an ERC4973 account-bound token

returns._0: The address of the owner bound to the ABT

ownerRevokeWithSignature(bytes32,bytes,u.details: Ref SoulboundCore.sol revokeWithSignature       This function grants the access to only the       deployer of the contract, unlike the core       that allows the function for anyone who has a       signature signed by the allowlistOwner.       This contract can be called by the deployer of the       contract [DaccredDeployer] but is also protected       as to the allowlistOwner must be the signer of the `sig.`
ownerRevokeWithSignature(bytes32,bytes,u.notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer].

payToReceiveToken(address,uint256).details: Allows the `_receiver` to pay the price of one token to        fully mint the pending token.
payToReceiveToken(address,uint256).notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer].

redeemMintedToken(address,uint256,uint25.details: For expired minted tokens, this function redeems them and makes       valid for another period of time.       Tokens must be expired for it to be redeemed.       Emits the {Redeemed} event.
redeemMintedToken(address,uint256,uint25.notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer].

redeemMintedTokenWithSignature(address,a.details: Allows the allowlistOwner to redeem an expired minted        token on behalf of the tokenOwner.
redeemMintedTokenWithSignature(address,a.notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer]           and the allowlistOwner.

redeemPendingToken(address,uint256,uint2.details: For expired pending tokens, this function redeems them and makes       valid for another period of time.       Tokens must be expired for it to be redeemed.       Emits the {Redeemed} event.
redeemPendingToken(address,uint256,uint2.notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer].

redeemPendingTokenWithSignature(address,.details: Allows the allowlistOwner to redeem an expired pending        token on behalf of the tokenOwner.
redeemPendingTokenWithSignature(address,.notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer]           and the allowlistOwner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call       `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.       NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner,       thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

revokeWithSignature(bytes32,bytes,uint25.details: Revokes the ownership of `tokenId` from the owner.       The token must exist and the signature must be signed the       allowlistOwner.       This emits the {RevokeWithSignature} event.

params.tokenId: Id of the token to revoke.

setBaseURI(address,string).details: Allows the `caller` (allowlistOwner) to set the baseURI.       This is really important when the caller wants to mint       Multiple tokens with the same base URI.
setBaseURI(address,string).notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer]           and the allowlistOwner.

setPrice(address,uint256).details: Allows `caller` to set `_price` as price of one token.
setPrice(address,uint256).notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer]           and the allowlistOwner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`).       Can only be called by the current owner.

verifySignature(bytes32,bytes).details: Returns true if the signer of signature `sig` is the `allowlistOwner`.       And false if otherwise.

verifySigner(address,bytes32,bytes).details: Returns true if the signer of `_signature` is `_signer`.

withdraw(address).details: Allows the allowlistowner to withdraw his funds to his wallet.
withdraw(address).notice: Callable by the deployer of this contract [DaccredDeployer]           and the allowlistOwner.

priceLimit.details: Price Limit [in eth] set by deploying contract.

tax.details: Tax for token redemptions.         15 represents 1.5% of total sales.

tokenPrice.details: Price of individual tokens, set by deployer.

totalSales.details: Total sales of tokens [Total tokens paid for].
